'''哈姆扎河'''（{{lang-pt|'''Rio Hamza'''}}）是[[巴西|巴西]]一個水流緩慢的地下[[蓄水層|蓄水層]]，发现于2011年，长约6000公里。河流的名字是非官方的，以发现者[[瓦利亚·哈姆扎|瓦利亚·哈姆扎]]命名。<ref name="Hamza Google/AFP">{{Cite web |url=http://www.google.com/hostednews/afp/article/ALeqM5iQD82Jq8W2DrAnyx26hkQnRZywlg?docId=CNG.52b18f33db4611dbaa6910ada765255d.01 |title=Scientists find underground river beneath Amazon |accessdate=2011-08-25 |year=2011 |archive-date=2012-11-23 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6CNwPzoRV?url=http://www.google.com/hostednews/afp/article/ALeqM5iQD82Jq8W2DrAnyx26hkQnRZywlg?docId=CNG.52b18f33db4611dbaa6910ada765255d.01 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

==描述==
哈姆扎河和[[亚马孙河|亚马孙河]]是[[亚马孙盆地|亚马孙盆地]]的两个主要的[[水系|水系]]，虽然哈姆扎河的[[容积流率|容积流率]]只有亚马孙河的3%——约3000立方米每秒。<ref name="Hamza Google/AFP" />它由西流向东，在地表以下4000米，流向与亚马孙河大致一致。<ref name="Hamza Fox News">{{Cite news |url=http://latino.foxnews.com/latino/news/2011/08/25/scientists-discover-underground-river-running-beneath-amazon/ |title=Scientists discover underground river running beneath the Amazon |accessdate=2011-08-25 |year=2011 |work=Fox News |date=2011-08-25 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120503102707/http://latino.foxnews.com/latino/news/2011/08/25/scientists-discover-underground-river-running-beneath-amazon/ |archivedate=2012-05-03 }}</ref>哈姆扎河注入[[大西洋|大西洋]]，<ref name="Hamza Hela Gotland">{{Cite web |url=http://www.helagotland.se/nyheter/default.aspx?articleid=7068974 |title=Underjordisk flod upptäckt |accessdate=2011-08-25 |year=2011 |publisher=Hela Gotland |location=SE |language=sv |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6CNwUDja8?url=http://www.helagotland.se/nyheter/default.aspx?articleid=7068974 |archive-date=2012-11-23 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>可能造成了亚马孙河口的低[[盐度|盐度]]。<ref name="Hamza Google/AFP" />它所含的水分是高盐度的。<ref name="Hamza BBC">{{Cite news |location=UK |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/science-environment-14693637 |publisher=BBC |first=Richard |last=Black |title=Subterranean Amazon river 'is not a river' |accessdate=2011-08-27 |date=August 27, 2011 |archive-date=2012-11-23 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6CNwT2if8?url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/science-environment-14693637 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

